==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|noyse}}, {{m|enm|noise}}, from {{der|en|fro|noise|t=a dispute, wrangle, strife, noise}}, of uncertain origin. According to some, from {{der|en|la|nausia}}, {{m|la|nausea|t=disgust, nausea}}; according to others, from {{der|en|la|noxia|t=hurt, harm, damage, injury}}; but neither explanation is satisfactory in regard to either form or sense.

